                <p><strong>If BAC is 0.08% or higher (even if under 21):</strong> You'll be charged with regular OWI (Operating While Intoxicated), which is a misdemeanor with much harsher penalties including up to 93 days in jail, up to $500 fine, 180-day license suspension, possible vehicle immobilization, and mandatory alcohol treatment.</p>

